parseNumber(item.memberDiscount);
``` 
to be like this:
```tundra
val priceAfterMemberDiscount = parseNumber(price) - parseNumber(item.member
parseNumber(item.memberDiscount);
```
Then, subtract `priceAfterMemberDiscount` from the initial `price` (which i
is a number parsed from item.price). This should give you the correct resul
result. Please note that Tundra does not have built-in support for parsing 
numbers from strings so I assume you already implemented parseNumber() func
function which converts string to number in your environment.
